  m_Name: Introduction
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogueText:
  - 
  - 'Flame: Hello.'
  - 'You: Hello... where are we?'
  - 'Flame: This is the afterlife.'
  - 'You: The afterlife? So I''m... I''m dead?'
  - 'Flame: Yes and you''re a soul collector.'
  - 'You: What does that mean?'
  - 'Flame: Well, your job is to go around and free souls from their eternal torment.'
  - 'You: Eternal torment? You mean that skull I picked up was suffering?'
  - 'Flame: Yes... I think. No flame really knows the truth, but we''ve all heard
    the stories of tormented souls being freed, then sharing the horrors they experienced.'
  - 'You: I need to free them! Where are they?'
  - 'Flame: Lost souls are everywhere. In order to travel between dimensions to save
    more souls, you have to save a certain amount of souls in the current dimension.'
  repeatingText: 'Flame: You need (current to win) souls to move on to the next dimension.
    There are still (current number) more souls in this dimension. You should try
    to save them all.'
  successText: 'Flame: You did it! The portal to the next dimension should be open
    now. It''s all the way on the top right cliff. There are (current number) souls
    left in this dimension.'
